        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Singapore International School - Dahisar"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Wasim Sayyed"
          },
          "datePublished": "2024-03-23",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Not sure why the fee structure is so secret, you have to pay non refundable Rs.15500 [ in 2024 ] for a school visit tour, and on fee policy page it's clearly written it also doesn't guarantee the admission,\n\nOk, I went to school directly anyway since it's near where I am currently living, asked watchmen for admission inquiry, he said go online and fill up the form, I said I know that at least tell me if seats are available he said, you have to fill the online form, I said what about fee?, at least let me inside already it was 35 degree heat that too in Ramadan, Yes I was fasting, he said fee also you will know once you fill online form. then I left.\n\nSo either this school is for elite people or those who don't mind giving away 15K for no reason, or maybe I am missing something?\n\nFunny part is, even If I pay Rs.15500 and they accepted my child, and then fee is 50 lakhs [ I can only assume ], as per there fee policy I need to pay it within 7 days.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
